    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "1 Corinthians",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 5,
        "summary": "The Church cannot fellowship sinners\u2014Christ, our passover, was sacrificed for us.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "It is reported commonly that there is fornication among you, and such fornication as is not so much as named among the Gentiles, that one should have his father's wife.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0sexual immorality. TG\u00a0Sexual Immorality.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 37
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And ye are puffed up, and have not rather mourned, that he that hath done this deed might be taken away from among you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 5:53 (53\u201356); 6:3.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 20
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For I verily, as absent in body, but present in spirit, have judged already, as though I were present, concerning him that hath so done this deed,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0as it were.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 113
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, when ye are gathered together, and my spirit, with the power of our Lord Jesus Christ,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a01\u00a0Cor. 5:4 \u2026 and have the Spirit, with\u00a0\u2026",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "To deliver such an one unto Satan for the destruction of the flesh, that the spirit may be saved in the day of the Lord Jesus.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Tim. 1:20; D&C 78:12 (11\u201312).",
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Punish.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 53
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 2:1; 19:3; 39:21; 45:12 (12\u201334); Moses 7:65 (59\u201367).",
                        "start": 104,
                        "end": 107
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Your glorying is not good. Know ye not that a little leaven leaveneth the whole lump?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0boasting. 1\u00a0Cor. 1:31; 3:21 (18\u201321).",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Purge out therefore the old leaven, that ye may be a new lump, as ye are unleavened. For even Christ our passover is sacrificed for us:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 43:11.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Bread, Unleavened.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 83
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Types of, in Anticipation; Passover.",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 113
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1444
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore let us keep the feast, not with old leaven, neither with the leaven of malice and wickedness; but with the unleavened bread of sincerity and truth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 12:14 (14\u201317).",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Leaven.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 52
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sincere.",
                        "start": 137,
                        "end": 146
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 128,
                        "end": 133
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I wrote unto you in an epistle not to company with fornicators:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Scriptures, Lost.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Thes. 3:6 (6, 11\u201315).",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0sexually immoral persons, male prostitutes. TG\u00a0Fornication.",
                        "start": 51,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Yet not altogether with the fornicators of this world, or with the covetous, or extortioners, or with idolaters; for then must ye needs go out of the world.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Covet.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0swindlers, robbers.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 92
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But now I have written unto you not to keep company, if any man that is called a brother be a fornicator, or covetous, or an idolater, or a railer, or a drunkard, or an extortioner; with such an one no not to eat.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 16:17.",
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 51
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Drunkenness.",
                        "start": 153,
                        "end": 161
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0not even.",
                        "start": 199,
                        "end": 205
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Jn. 1:10.",
                        "start": 209,
                        "end": 212
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For what have I to do to judge them also that are without? do not ye judge them that are within?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "GR\u00a0outside, foreign, not belonging.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 57
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Cor. 6:1.",
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But them that are without God judgeth. Therefore put away from among yourselves that wicked person.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}